NAME
    strings(1)          - find printable strings in a file

SYNOPSIS
    strings  [ -o ]  [ -number ]  [ file ]

DESCRIPTION
    The "file", or standard input if "file" is not specified,
    is scanned for possible character strings. A "string" is
    a sequence of 4 or more printable ASCII characters followed
    by a '\0', '\n' or '\r'.

    This information might be useful for identifying an object 
    file.

OPTIONS
    -o		Also display the character offset of the start
		of the string from the beginning of the file.
		Thus, the first character of the file is at
		offset zero (0). The offset is printed in decimal.

    -number	Minimum sequence length which is considered a
		string (the default is 4). Note that the program
		truncates all strings over 78 characters, to
		aid readability of the output.

SEE ALSO
    od(1)
